==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Nomenclature
<hw>No"men*cla`ture</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>nomenclatura</ets>: cf. F. <ets>nomenclature</ets>. See
<er>Nomenclator</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A name.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A vocabulary, dictionary, or glossary.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The technical names used in any particular branch of
science or art, or by any school or individual; <as>as, the
<ex>nomenclature</ex> of botany or of chemistry; the
<ex>nomenclature</ex> of <persfn>Lavoisier</persfn> and his
associates.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nomial</ent>⟦br⟧
